to be the example here, I can make that a little bigger for you.

00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:11.419
So you can kind of peek into your Snowflake, again, you can take advantage of anything

00:12:11.419 --> 00:12:17.700
we build for VS Code, you get access to that now inside of Positron.

00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:20.940
There's a lot of other kind of cool little bells and whistles under the hood in terms

00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:25.979
of connecting to Snowflake, that's very, very seamless, but you get access to all this stuff

00:12:25.979 --> 00:12:26.979
as well.

00:12:26.979 --> 00:12:31.419
And from here, I'm not going to go too much through this, this is just an example of kind

00:12:31.419 --> 00:12:39.299
of working with your data, all running in R. I'm importing some macroeconomic data that

00:12:39.299 --> 00:12:43.179
I pulled off of our marketplace, so that marketplace where all that financial data

00:12:43.179 --> 00:12:44.179
comes in.

00:12:44.179 --> 00:12:48.219
We have tons of free data on there, especially free macroeconomic data, so if you want to

00:12:48.219 --> 00:12:53.500
replicate this, you can kind of pull down that free macroeconomic data.

00:12:53.500 --> 00:13:00.179
Once I've pulled it into Positron, frankly, hopefully this is going to look really familiar

00:13:00.179 --> 00:13:01.179
to you all.

00:13:01.179 --> 00:13:05.140
I can just work as I normally would in R. So I'm going to do some really light wrangling

