it's something that, I mean, I've been working in the R world for a really long time.

00:15:16.059 --> 00:15:19.820
We've heard for a long time, R in production, does it work, does it not work, should we

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:22.419
just refactor everything into Python?

00:15:22.419 --> 00:15:26.500
What this partnership does is it makes it a very smooth glide path for getting your

00:15:26.500 --> 00:15:29.380
work in R into, quote-unquote, production.

00:15:29.380 --> 00:15:32.820
I think production means a lot of different things.

00:15:32.820 --> 00:15:38.539
I bucket being something in production as is it affecting the decision-making of your

00:15:38.539 --> 00:15:40.179
company in some way?

00:15:40.179 --> 00:15:43.419
So is it driving outcomes, is it driving decisions, right?

00:15:43.419 --> 00:15:48.260
There's a few different ways that this work can, from that definition, get into production

00:15:48.260 --> 00:15:49.380
of what you're doing.

00:15:49.380 --> 00:15:56.700
So one we looked at earlier, which is Snowflake has this concept of the internal marketplace.

00:15:56.700 --> 00:15:59.820
So I talked to you all about the external marketplace where data providers can come

00:15:59.820 --> 00:16:05.500
share data, places like Bloomberg and S&P Global can share data across what they're

00:16:05.500 --> 00:16:06.500
doing.

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:10.340
We have that exact same functionality inside Snowflake, but internally.

00:16:10.340 --> 00:16:14.859
So if you want to share any data products that you've built internally with other teams,

00:16:14.859 --> 00:16:16.780
you can do that via our marketplace.

00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:21.179
This is massively popular and important inside of asset management right now, because there

00:16:21.179 --> 00:16:27.059
are so many data teams doing so much work, and they literally ship them CSV files and

00:16:27.059 --> 00:16:29.260
Excel files, and it's an absolute nightmare.

00:16:29.260 --> 00:16:33.539
If you use the internal marketplace on Snowflake, all the work that you've done in Posit, you

00:16:33.539 --> 00:16:35.859
can share back to other teams.

00:16:35.859 --> 00:16:39.460
Second way this enables your work getting into production is we have in Snowflake a

00:16:39.460 --> 00:16:40.460
native feature store.

00:16:40.460 --> 00:16:42.179
So that's what I'm kind of highlighting here.

00:16:42.179 --> 00:16:46.320
So if you've just done feature engineering, and you want to kind of take that orbital

00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:49.979
package which translates what you've done into SQL code, you can take advantage of our

00:16:49.979 --> 00:16:50.979
feature store.

00:16:50.979 --> 00:16:55.700
So that's like big thing number two, because I'm sure as you all know, with machine learning,

00:16:55.700 --> 00:16:58.859
feature engineering is really the most important step in machine learning.

00:16:58.859 --> 00:17:03.140
So via Snowflake, all that work you've done in R, all the cool work you've done with recipes

00:17:03.140 --> 00:17:07.660
and anything, any wrangling you may have done, if you want to turn that into production level

00:17:07.660 --> 00:17:11.380
features, you can use our native feature store.

00:17:11.579 --> 00:17:17.660
The third way is that in private preview right now, but coming very, very soon, is an integration

00:17:17.660 --> 00:17:18.939
with Posit Connect.

00:17:18.939 --> 00:17:22.180
So if you want to use all that work you've done to drive dashboards that are going to

00:17:22.180 --> 00:17:26.300
be kind of seamlessly updated as data gets updated inside Snowflake, that's all going

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:28.739
to be possible very soon.

00:17:28.739 --> 00:17:32.920
I think if you can get access to the private preview feature, it's already possible.

00:17:32.920 --> 00:17:36.780
But that'll be obviously GA very, very soon.

00:17:36.780 --> 00:17:38.140
So that's my talk.

00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:40.939
That's about the partnership between Posit and Snowflake.

00:17:40.939 --> 00:17:42.859
It's super exciting.

00:17:42.859 --> 00:17:47.180
To me, Posit's the best data science tooling in the world, Snowflake's the best data warehouse

00:17:47.180 --> 00:17:48.180
in the world.

00:17:48.180 --> 00:17:52.739
You can put them both together now, get endless compute with all of your data.

00:17:52.739 --> 00:17:53.739
So thank you.

00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:56.180
I think I might have time for one or two questions.

