00:18:16.699 --> 00:18:17.699
Yeah.

00:18:17.699 --> 00:18:21.979
So you would need to give them access to Snowflake is the answer right now.

00:18:21.979 --> 00:18:28.260
I think coming on the roadmap is the ability to use probably OAuth to do that, but for

00:18:28.260 --> 00:18:30.459
now you have to give them access to Snowflake.

00:18:30.459 --> 00:18:31.459
Okay.

00:18:31.459 --> 00:18:32.739
Thank you.

00:18:32.739 --> 00:18:36.819
Another question, is the main benefit of Snowflake for big data?

00:18:36.819 --> 00:18:42.180
What is the main benefit for, say, something like survey market research, smaller, and

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:44.660
where each survey is unique?

00:18:44.660 --> 00:18:50.939
So I think in general, the benefit of Snowflake is having a unified data platform, right?

00:18:50.939 --> 00:18:55.300
So big data, small data, you still get those benefits.

00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:58.780
And if you're just working with small data, then it's not going to cost you nearly as

00:18:58.780 --> 00:19:00.859
much to use Snowflake, but you're still going to get all the benefits.

00:19:00.859 --> 00:19:05.939
So I think actually if you're using smaller data, you're going to actually get all the

00:19:05.939 --> 00:19:07.780
same benefits, but at a much lower cost.

00:19:07.780 --> 00:19:10.380
So I think that's actually a good example of using Snowflake.

00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:11.380
Yeah.

